  "text": "The IAT is a computerized reaction time test with strong psychometric properties [CITATION_1] where participants sort target stimuli into superordinate categories to assess the relative strength of associations between concepts. Research assistants administered the social competence and behavioral competence IATs in counterbalanced order. For the social competence IAT, words were used as stimuli for the categories self (me, myself, I) versus others (them, her, him), and three pictures of peer-accepted children versus three pictures of peer-rejected children were used as stimuli for the categories accepted versus rejected. Research assistants first ensured that children understood which stimuli represented each category before administering the critical trials.",
